# jemdoc: menu{MENU}{bio.html}

Gongguo Tang is an Associate Professor in the [http://electrical.mines.edu/ Department of Electrical Engineering] at [http://www.mines.edu Colorado School of Mines] since Spring 2014. Before that, he was a visiting scholar at [http://simons.berkeley.edu Simons Institute for the Theory of Computing] at University of California, Berkeley and a postdoc working with [http://nowak.ece.wisc.edu Professor Robert Nowak] at the University of Wisconsin-Madison and [http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/~brecht/ Professor Benjamin Recht]  at the University of California, Berkeley from 2011 to 2013. He received his PhD in Electrical Engineering from Washington University in St. Louis under the supervision of [http://www.ese.wustl.edu/~nehorai/ Professor Arye Nehorai].
